        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 5:22PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Woodstock, or 14 miles southwest of Bessemer, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hoover, Alabaster, Bessemer, Helena, Montevallo, Lake View,
Brookwood, Coaling, Vance, Woodstock, West Blocton, Tannehill
Ironworks State Park, Abernant, American Village, Maylene, Hoover
Metropolitan Stadium, University Of Montevallo, Mercedes Benz Of
Alabama, North Bibb, and Joe Tucker Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
